message.body: Oh good idea. Is it a lot of stuff?
￼Here's about half of it
Could be worse.
I like the fact that you have two different sizes of Tide.
Yeah. I just have been used to living in one room for a long time. Lol well I don't have an in house washer so I'd rather haul the tiny one than the full
I don't blame you. How many trips do you have to make?
I'm guessing 2 after my dad gets here to help with my bed. Making the first one now with my brother.
Thank you kind stranger. http://imgur.com/a/XJtfN
Who's chopping onions in here?!

￼So funny story with this pic. I always had the idea to pack all of my clothes in these contractor bags. It's so easy. Pull off of the rack and into the bag then just as easy to undo. I finally get around to helping my sister pack since I graduated before her and we would always have different schedules. She's like ugh I hate packing my shirts. I ask why? It's such an easy thing. She's like gosh you have to take off each hanger, fold everything nicely, pack it, move, unpack, maybe iron, then redo each hanger. I find a contractor bag and drop all of her stuff in less than a minute. She freaks the fuck out. WHY HAVEN'T I BEEN DOING THAT ALL OF THESE YEARS. WHAT THE SHIT?!
Hahahah! You must be somewhat experienced by now with the amount of tunes you moved!
And onions?
Where was that?
I passed out at three different points today. Just took a 3-4 hour nap.
Haha surprise surprise. I don't know where that was. It was something I saw and it's always touching to see that kindness
That was nice. I was also referring to the onions?
It's a corny reference to shedding tears because when you cut onions..
Ohhhhh!
Sneaky sneaky.
So are you finished moving?
Mostly. Tomorrow will be unpacking and settling in
How's the babysitting marathon?
I'm waking to des them so that they'll go to bed.
*feed
My mom is hanging out with them while I'm on my laptop. Planning to stay up for the new few hoursz
*hours, but "hoursz" works too hahah.
Lol. You wasted?
If it's on water and sleep deprivation, then yes.
I figured as much.
Is this going to be the first night in your apartment?
No. There is no power because they didn't tell me I needed to call peco. So I'll have to handle that tomorrow. I'm in valley forge at the moment but I'll be sleeping at my parent's place
Power is pretty important. The dark is scary?
Not as much. I just couldn't see to get settled in lol
There's that to too hahah!
We just lost an hour!
Oh that was tonight!!
Where did the last hour of our lives go???
Indeed. Nowhere. It just disappeared
